text: I love communicating with intelligent animals. Like there is an old dog living on the dead end street to my gym and when I pass by him I sniff the air in his direction to get his attention and then look at him in the eyes and blink slowly and he blinks too afterwards. Genius dog!

It's such a simple gesture, just closing your eyes a bit to show you trust that he won't use the opportunity to jump at you, he understands and repeats to show he trusts me too. You can tell he "gets it" and understands the meaning of the interaction. Cross-species communication.

The other day I was waiting to cross the street at a pedestrian traffic light with like 20 normies waiting behind me and there were 2 policemen a few meters down the sidewalk standing next to their csr. There were no cars coming on the street, but the traffic light was still red.

Normally I would just run across, but the cops were looking at me, so I just sorta sticked my foot forward and dangled it above the street without touching it, wiggling it in the air, while looking at the policeman in the eyes. He slowly shook his head and made a "nuh-uh" noise.
He sorta giggled too. Policemen can def tell that I'm not a "doing crime" type (maybe something white collar like insider trading at worst) so they always just kek at my antics
